    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="124"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d124">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_HHL1">Hopkins</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_HWA2" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Presidents Special Assistant</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_HHL1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hopkins</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d124fn1">Sent by the United States Naval
                        Attaché, Moscow, via Navy channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">routine</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-12">12 November
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Personal and secret for <persName corresp="#p_HHL1">Hopkins</persName> from
                        <persName corresp="#p_HWA2">Harriman</persName>.</p>
                <p>Since cabling the President last night<note n="2" xml:id="d124fn2">Telegram of
                        November 12, 1943, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_80">p.
                            80</ref>.</note> about our joining him at Cairo on the 22nd I have been
                    wondering whether it would not be of value for us to make our reports prior to
                    the meeting with <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName>. We have of
                    course considerable information both military and political of reactions to and
                    developments since the Conference broke up which perhaps should be discussed
                        beforehand.<note n="3" xml:id="d124fn3">See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>,
                            <ref target="#pg_81">p. 81</ref>, footnote 4.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
